WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.775 --> 00:09.522
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.182 --> 00:18.353
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.473 --> 00:27.986
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:29.474 --> 00:36.841
The glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part three.

00:38.542 --> 00:51.154
For God, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, hath shined in our hearts, to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

00:51.174 --> 00:59.442
2 Corinthians chapter 4 verse 6.

00:59.778 --> 01:10.269
I am led to see his glory in the outgoing of his great heart, for he is altogether unselfish and unsparingly communicative.

01:11.730 --> 01:18.497
We may conceive a period when the Eternal God dwelt alone and had not begun to create.

01:19.578 --> 01:27.186
He must have been inconceivably blessed, but he was not content to be unwrapped within himself.

01:27.714 --> 01:30.217
and to enjoy perfect bliss alone.

01:31.299 --> 01:38.889
He began to create, and probably formed innumerable beings long before this world came into existence.

01:39.870 --> 01:44.677
And he did this that he might multiply beings capable of happiness.

01:46.319 --> 01:55.031
He delighted to indulge his heart by deeds of beneficence, manifesting the inherent goodness of his nature.

01:56.132 --> 01:57.554
In whatever God is doing,

01:58.050 --> 02:00.913
He is consulting the happiness of His creatures.

02:02.055 --> 02:06.840
Being in Himself independent of all, He loves to bless others.

02:07.881 --> 02:11.605
He is living, we speak with awe in His presence.

02:11.625 --> 02:20.655
He is living even He not unto Himself, but living in the lives of others, rejoicing in the joy of His creatures.

02:21.917 --> 02:26.482
This is His glory, and is it not to be seen most evidently

02:26.786 --> 02:33.075
in Christ Jesus, who saved others, himself he could not save.

02:34.657 --> 02:38.783
Do you not see the great unselfish glory of God in Christ Jesus?

02:39.884 --> 02:42.348
When did he ever live unto himself?

02:43.389 --> 02:46.634
What single act of his had a selfish purpose?

02:47.595 --> 02:50.279
What word ever sought his own honour?

02:51.381 --> 02:55.186
In what deed did he consult his own aggrandizement?

02:56.034 --> 03:02.000
Neither in life nor in death did Christ live within himself.

03:02.020 --> 03:05.064
He lived for his people and died for them.

03:06.185 --> 03:07.967
See the glory of God in this.

03:07.987 --> 03:19.019
There are two things I have noticed in the glory of God whenever my soul has been saturated with it, and these I have seen in Jesus.

03:20.360 --> 03:22.162
I have stood upon a lofty hill

03:22.594 --> 03:34.305
and looked abroad upon the landscape and seen hill and dale and wood and field, and I have felt as if God had gone forth and spread his presence over all.

03:35.066 --> 03:37.608
I have felt the outflow of deity.

03:38.509 --> 03:52.562
There was not a pleasant tree, nor a silvery stream, nor a cornfield ripening for the harvest, nor mount shaggy with pines, nor heath purple with heather, but seemed a glow,

03:52.706 --> 03:53.367
with God.

03:54.568 --> 03:58.794
Even as the sun pours itself over all things, so does God.

03:59.995 --> 04:08.626
And in the hum of an insect, as well as in the crash of a thunderbolt, we hear a voice saying, God is here.

04:10.028 --> 04:16.356
God has gone forth out of Himself into the creation and filled all things.

04:17.578 --> 04:21.042
It's not this, the feeling of the heart in the presence of Christ,

04:21.602 --> 04:26.507
When we come near Him, He is the all-pervading Spirit.

04:27.468 --> 04:31.693
In any of the scenes which Jesus appears, He is omnipresent.

04:32.654 --> 04:37.239
Who but He is at Bethlehem or at Nazareth or at Jerusalem?

04:38.661 --> 04:40.783
Who but He is in the world?

04:41.884 --> 04:47.430
Is not He to ask the everybody, the one and only person of His age?

04:48.611 --> 04:50.994
I cannot think of Caesar or Rome

04:51.298 --> 05:00.948
or all the myriads that dwell on the face of the earth as being anything more than small figures in the background of the picture when Jesus is before me.

05:02.490 --> 05:07.234
He is to my mind most clearly the fullness filling all in all.

05:08.256 --> 05:18.386
All the accessories of any scene in which he appears are submerged in the flood of glory which flows from his all subduing presence.

05:19.234 --> 05:23.520
surely the fullness of the glory of God was in Christ.

05:25.263 --> 05:29.569
But you must have had another thought when you have felt the glory of God in nature.

05:30.851 --> 05:35.037
You must have felt the in drawing of all things towards God.

05:36.359 --> 05:41.427
You have felt created things rising unto God as steps to His throne.

05:41.447 --> 05:49.138
As you have gazed with rapture on the landscape, every tree and hill has seemed

05:49.282 --> 05:57.993
to drift towards God, to tend towards Him, to return in fact to Him from whom it came.

05:59.314 --> 06:01.958
Is it not just so in the life of Christ?

06:02.738 --> 06:11.189
He seems to be drawing all things to Himself, gathering together all things in one in His own personality.

06:13.211 --> 06:18.738
Some of these things will not move, but yet His attraction has fallen on them.

06:19.490 --> 06:29.087
while others fly with speed to Him according to His Word, I, if I be lifted up, will draw all men unto Me.

06:29.127 --> 06:42.770
Thus those observations of the glory of God which have been suggested to us by nature are also abundantly verified in Christ, and we are sure that the glory is the same.

06:44.802 --> 06:51.130
I cannot express my thoughts to you so clearly and vividly as I would like, but this I know.

06:51.190 --> 07:10.775
If you ever get a vision of the glory of God in nature, and if you then turn your thoughts towards the Lord's Christ, you will see that the same God is in Him as in the visible universe, and that the same glory shines in Him only more clearly.

07:11.936 --> 07:13.138
There is one God.

07:13.634 --> 07:17.719
and that one God is gloriously manifested in Christ Jesus.

07:18.880 --> 07:28.112
No man hath seen God at any time, the only begotten Son, which is in the bosom of the Father, he hath declared him.

07:30.194 --> 07:36.342
Let us now treat this thought of the glory of God in the person of Christ by way of experience.

07:37.704 --> 07:40.928
Have you ever heard of Christ's doctrine in your soul?

07:42.109 --> 07:42.770
If so,

07:43.010 --> 07:53.203
You have felt it to be divine, for your heart has perceived its moral and spiritual glory, and you have concluded that God is in it of a truth.

07:54.985 --> 08:00.772
Has your heart heard the voice of Christ speaking peace and pardon through his blood?

08:02.234 --> 08:05.999
If so, you have known him to be Lord of all.

08:07.280 --> 08:09.703
Did you ever see the fullness of his atonement?

08:10.745 --> 08:11.826
Then you have felt

08:12.066 --> 08:15.709
that God Himself was there reconciling the world unto Himself.

08:17.011 --> 08:22.396
You have understood the union of the two titles, God our Savior.

08:23.977 --> 08:31.604
Beloved, you have often felt your Lord's presence, and you have been admitted into intimate communion with Him.

08:33.046 --> 08:42.034
Then I know that a profound awe has crept over you, which has made you fall at His feet, and in the lowliest reverence of your Spirit,

08:42.338 --> 08:45.281
you have owned him to be Lord and God.

08:46.743 --> 09:06.344
But when he has bent over you in love and said fear not, when he has opened his heart to you and shown you how dear you are to him, then the rapture you have felt has been so divine that you have beyond all question known him to be God.

09:07.906 --> 09:11.890
There are times when the elevating influence of the presence of Christ

09:12.034 --> 09:16.079
has put his Godhead beyond the possibility of question.

09:17.240 --> 09:33.979
When we have felt that all the truth we ever heard before had no effect upon us compared with the truth that is in him, that all the spirits in the world were ineffectual to stir us till his spirit came into contact with our spirit.

09:35.140 --> 09:39.986
In this manner, his omnipotent, all subduing, elevating love

09:40.386 --> 09:45.113
has proved him to be none other than very God of very God.

09:46.976 --> 09:51.864
Thus we have spoken of the supremely precious object of Christian knowledge.

09:53.767 --> 09:59.996
Secondly, let us spend a few words in noticing the nature of this knowledge.

10:01.138 --> 10:06.266
How and in what respects do we know the glory of God in the face of Christ?

10:07.828 --> 10:08.850
Briefly first,

10:09.250 --> 10:10.551
We know it by faith.

10:11.833 --> 10:18.721
Upon the testimony of the infallible word, we believe and are sure that God is in Christ Jesus.

10:19.762 --> 10:23.786
The Lord hath spoken and said, This is my beloved Son.

10:23.846 --> 10:25.108
Hear ye Him.

10:26.549 --> 10:34.438
We accept as a settled fact the Godhead of the Lord Jesus, and our soul never permits a question upon it.

10:35.700 --> 10:37.842
We know that the Son of God is come,

10:38.146 --> 10:48.956
and hath given us an understanding that we may know him that is true, and we are in him that is true, even in his Son Jesus Christ.

10:49.917 --> 10:53.280
This is the true God and eternal life.

10:54.902 --> 11:07.474
Knowing our Lord's divinity by faith, we next have used our perceptive faculty, and by consideration and meditation, we perceive that his life furnishes abundant evidence

11:07.618 --> 11:08.699
that He was God.

11:09.501 --> 11:11.704
For God's glory shines in that life.

11:12.725 --> 11:23.700
The more carefully we pay attention to the details given us by the four evangelists, the more is our understanding persuaded that no mere man stands before us.

11:24.481 --> 11:36.818
If, my brothers and sisters, your spiritual nature was set this task to try and describe how God would act if He were here, what God would be if He became incarnate

11:36.962 --> 11:38.023
and dwelt among us.

11:39.045 --> 11:42.670
I am sure you would not have been able to imagine the life of Christ.

11:43.991 --> 11:51.061
But if someone had brought to you the description given by the evangelists, you would have said, My task is done.

11:51.101 --> 11:57.049
This indeed is a noble conception of God manifest in the flesh.

11:58.511 --> 12:04.178
I do not say that the wise men of this world would suppose God to have thus behaved.

12:04.994 --> 12:11.921
For their suppositions are sure to be the reverse of the simple, unaffected, open-hearted conduct of Jesus.

12:12.942 --> 12:21.630
But this, I say, that the pure in heart will at once see that the acts of Christ are like the doings of God.

12:22.511 --> 12:27.576
He hath done exactly what a pure intelligence might suppose God would have done.

12:28.757 --> 12:34.002
The more we have studied, the more we have seen the glory of God in Christ.

12:36.098 --> 12:45.491
And now we have come rather further than this, for we feel an inward consciousness that the deity is in Christ Jesus.

12:46.732 --> 12:58.228
It is not merely that we have believed it, and that we somewhat perceive it by observation, but we have come into contact with Christ and have known therefore that He is God.

12:59.470 --> 13:05.618
We love Him, and we also love God, and we perceive that these two are one.

13:06.338 --> 13:20.879
And the more we love truth and holiness and love, which are great traits in the character of God, the more we see of these in Christ Jesus, it is by the heart that we know God and Christ.

13:21.901 --> 13:27.489
And as our affections are purified, we become sensible of God's presence in Christ.

13:28.991 --> 13:33.778
Moreover, there is one other thing that has happened to us while we have been looking at our Lord.

13:34.530 --> 13:36.553
We begin to grow like Him.

13:37.834 --> 13:42.921
Our beholding Him has purified the eye which has gazed on His purity.

13:44.042 --> 13:51.391
His brightness has helped our eyesight so that we see much already and shall yet see more.

13:52.713 --> 13:59.522
The light of the sun blinds us, but the light of Jesus Christ strengthens the eye.

14:00.543 --> 14:03.026
We expect that as we grow in grace,

14:03.266 --> 14:13.201
We shall behold more and more of God's glory, but we shall see it best in the well-beloved, even in Jesus Christ our Lord.

14:14.543 --> 14:17.167
What a sight of God we shall enjoy in heaven!

14:18.269 --> 14:28.665
We are tending that way, and as we get nearer and nearer, our sight and vision of the glory of God in Christ is every day increased.

14:29.666 --> 14:30.588
We know it then.

14:31.249 --> 14:32.050
We know it.

14:32.194 --> 14:32.975
We believe it.

14:33.175 --> 14:34.336
We are conscious of it.

14:34.757 --> 14:36.218
We are affected by it.

14:36.579 --> 14:38.260
We are transformed by it.

14:39.001 --> 14:46.790
And thus, at this day, we have the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

14:48.411 --> 14:49.693
Thank you for listening, friends.

